Position Details
• Position Type: Internship
• Work Location: On-site / Remote (Flexible)
• Compensation: Paid internship (rate based on skill level)

Responsibilities
• Assist in developing and maintaining smart contracts.
• Support senior engineers with testing, debugging, and documentation.
• Learn to review Solidity code for security, gas efficiency, and best practices.
• Work closely with the frontend and backend team to understand full dApp architecture.

Requirements
• Basic understanding of Solidity and EVM concepts.
• Familiarity with web3 tooling (Hardhat, OpenZeppelin, etc.)
• Strong motivation to learn blockchain engineering.
• Ability to follow technical instructions and contribute to team tasks.
• English communication skills.

Nice to Have
• Small personal Solidity projects or GitHub repos.
• Understanding of ERC20/721 standards.
• Basic knowledge of blockchain security tools like Slither or MythX.
• Experience reading existing smart contracts.

Hiring Process
You will go through two simple steps:
• Technical Assignment: to evaluate your foundational Solidity knowledge.
• Technical Interview: to review your code, learning ability, and problem-solving approach.

If both go well, you will join us as a Junior Engineer / Intern with a clear growth path.

Benefits
• Paid internship
• Remote work environment
• Training and certification support
• Ability to move into a full-time engineer role
• Flexible working schedule
• Opportunities to learn directly from senior blockchain developers